atpx.minecraft

Interface DataValues

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    IntoChest

    public interface DataValues
    DataValues interface stores data mappings of Minecraft items necessary for IntoChest to function.

    Not intended to be serialized.

    Author:
    Jeff Lee

    • Field Detail

      • NOTSTACKABLE

        static final java.util.List<java.lang.Integer> NOTSTACKABLE
        NOTSTACKABLE is a List that contains the decimal IDs of Minecraft items that are not stackable.

        Cannot be modified at runtime.

      • TYPEDEPENDANTSTACKABLE

        static final java.util.List<java.lang.Integer> TYPEDEPENDANTSTACKABLE
        TYPEDEPENDANTSTACKABLE is a List that contains the decimal IDs of Minecraft items that cannot be stacked depending on the data value of the item.

        Example: All wool items have an ID of 35, but items with data value 0 are white wool while items with data value 1 are orange wool. The two cannot be stacked together.

        Cannot be modified at runtime.

      • GRPDATAVALUES

        static final java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String>> GRPDATAVALUES
        GRPDATAVALUES is a Map that contains the names of collective items and a list of qualifying item IDs of the collection.

        Key: Name of group
        Value: List of item IDs that belong in the group

        Example: The group name 'armor' contains the item IDs of all helmets, chestplate, leggings, boots, etc. in the game.

        Cannot be modified at runtime.

      • ITEMNAMES

        static final java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> ITEMNAMES
        ITEMNAMES is a Map that contains item IDs/data values and their corresponding user-friendly name.

        Key: Item ID and item data value delimited by a pipe
        Value: The user-friendly name of the item

        Example: "1|2" where 1 is the item ID and 2 is the data value is the key that maps to "polished granite".

        Cannot be modified at runtime.

      • SHORTITEMNAMES

        static final java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> SHORTITEMNAMES
        SHORTITEMNAMES is a Map that contains item IDs/data values and their corresponding short name defined for IntoChest.

        The short name is derived by:
        1. Take the first character of each word that is not the last word of the user-friendly name.
        2. Take the first four characters of the last word of the user-friendly name.

        Note that 5% of items have collisions with each other. In such events, the short name is required to add more characters from the first word of the user-friendly name.

        Key: Item ID and item data value delimited by a pipe
        Value: The short name of the item

        Example: "1|2" where 1 is the item ID and 2 is the data value is the key that maps to "pgran", which is "polished granite". 'p' is the first character of a word that is not the last word. "gran" is the first four characters of the last word.

        Example: "6|5" is the key that maps to "dowplan", which is "dark oak wood plank". 'd' is the first character of a word that is not the last word (first word). 'o' is the first character of a word that is not the last word (second word). 'w' is the first character of a word that is not the last word (third word). "plan" is the first four characters of the last word.

        Example: "35|6" is the key that maps to "piwool" (pink wool). "35|10" is the key that maps to "puwool" (purple wool). Regular derivation of a short name would result in both items being "pwool", which is not acceptable. We must add an extra character from the first word of the friendly-name. We add 'i' to pink wool and 'u' to purple wool.

        Cannot be modified at runtime.
